gomodel:SYNGO_541  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig. 6 MAGI2 interacts with NMDA\nLiteral\n\"The anti-S-SCAM antibody coimmunoprecipitated NMDAR1, whereas the preimmune serum did not.This result indicates that S-SCAM interacts with NMDA receptors in vivo.\"\nFig. 7 MAGI2 colocalyzed with PSD-95\nLiteral\n\"To examine the distribution of S-SCAM in neurons, we double-stained primary cultured rat hippocampal neurons on day 14 in the combination of anti-S-SCAM antibody with either anti-NMDAR1 or anti-PSD- 95/SAP90 antibody. The staining pattern of S-SCAM was similar to that of PSD-95/SAP90, which was detected in the cell body as well as at the dendrites (Fig. 7A). S-SCAM showed\ndistributions similar to those of NMDAR1 at dendrites (Fig.7B). Because SAPAP was distributed in a manner similar to that of PSD-95/SAP90 (Fig. 7C), S-SCAM was considered to be distributed in a manner similar to SAPAP.\nFig. 8\nLiteral\n\"We also determined the distribution of S-SCAM in the subcellular fractions of rat brain by the immunoblotting with the anti-S-SCAM antibody. The signals detected with the antibody were distributed in both the cytosolic synaptosomal (S2) and\ncrude synaptosomal pellet (P2) fractions (Fig. 8).. Experimental description: Co-immunoprecipitation was done in rat brain\nLiteral from Results\n\"To determine whether S-SCAM interacts with NMDA receptors in the native environment in neurons, we performed the immunoprecipitation of S-SCAM from the detergent extract of the crude rat brain synaptosomes.\"\nExperiment of immunohistochemistry are made in rat.\nLiteral from results\n\"To examine the distribution of S-SCAM in neurons, we double-stained primary cultured rat hippocampal neurons\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2949-9725" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0662-9523" ;
        dc:date           "2017-05-24" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_541" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

